defaultLack of information in inspection reportsdefault&#xa0;
default1. How much time was spent in the home? 
default2. How many inspectors? 
default3. The name of the inspector 
default4. The time of the inspection 
default5. How many relatives were spoken with or involved in the inspection via a survey? 
default6. Whether there is a registered manager in post? 
default7. If so, the name and qualifications of the manager 
default8. If none, to say so and give the reasons 
default9. Plus provider’s plan to deal with the vacancy and appoint a new manager 
default10. Which regulations were found to have been breached during the inspection? 
default11. The specific powers being used to take enforcement action 
default12. Plus the time-table for this 
default13. Which regulations are still in breach from any previous inspections and reasons, if any, for any continued breach 
default14. If so, what further enforcement action will be taken? 
default15. The number of complaints received, what they were about and whether or not they have been resolved? 
default16. Any safeguarding concerns and if so, what about? and to whom referred? 
default17. Some detail about the staffing ratio in the home and 
default18. Whether there are any stimulating activities
